cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG 

This paper focuses on the communication between humans and robots in the context of shared autonomy, which involves both human input and robot decision-making. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the use of domain knowledge and preferences, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of plans, which is related to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses language and communication, which suggests a connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-offs between efficiency and cognitive load, which suggests a connection to cs.LG (Learning).
